post_text:
Did you know?
April is Child Abuse Prevention Month. As a trauma responsive organization, we believe that every child has the right to a safe childhood free of violence. We know that many of the young people we serve have experienced some type of abuse which impacts their development, sense of security and overall world view. Across Trailblazers, Stamford Academy and the 4 Domus Family Advocate programs in the Stamford Public Schools, 90 students (21%) have had some involvement with the Department of Children and Families due to suspected abuse or neglect at some point in their lives. Please join us in promoting safety, awareness and dialogue so that we can make a difference in the lives of those we serve. Parent education and community support are critical to promoting strong and healthy families.

On Friday, April 5th, Please join us in wearing BLUE to help support our cause 😀

post_text:
Reminder!

Trailblazers Academy Middle School alums! Would you or your parent be willing to speak about your experience at Trailblazers? You're a success, you're happy, you're working or in school...come tell the State Board of Education why you think other kids with potential like yours but who've struggled should have the same chance as YOU. The hearing to renew our State charter is on December 20th from 6pm to 8pm at JM Wright Tech. If you're available and want to know more, please email Mr. Baker or Mr. McGuire ('cause you know they want to hear from you anywaaaaay), or call the school at 203.977.5690 (and talk to Ms. Donald, who'll be so happy to hear from you!). Mr. Baker: cbaker (at)domuskids.org; Mr. McGuire: mmcguire (at)domuskids.org. Please SHARE with other former Trailblazers students :) Thanks! <3

post_text: Te invitamos a visitar nuestra escuela intermedia para mas informacion sobre el programa bilingüe que se va ofrecer el año escolar entrante, 2015-2016, este Miercoles, 10 de Junio a las 6pm. El Programa Bilingüe o ELL, es un servicio escolar adicional proporcionado en muchas escuelas para que los niños que están aprendiendo Inglés triunfen en su clase de nivel de grado. Tenemos clases pequeñas y íntimas que proporcionan para su hijo la atención que él o ella necesita para sobresalir académicamente. La Academia de Trailblazers enseña a grados 6, 7, y 8.
